%N A394608 Decimal expansion of the median of the distribution of distances between two points in a unit square.
%C A394608 The median of the probability density function f(x) = 4*x*(Pi/2 - 2*x + x^2/2) for x <= 1, and 4*x*(arcsin(1/x) - arccos(1/x) + 2*sqrt(x^2-1) - (x^2+2)/2) for 1 <= x <= sqrt(2) (Ghosh, 1951).
%C A394608 The second root of 3*x^4 - 16*x^3 + 6*Pi*x^2 - 3 = 0.
%H A394608 Birendranath Ghosh, <a href="https://archive.org/details/dli.calcutta.11610/page/17/mode/1up">Random distances within a rectangle and between two rectangles</a>, Bulletin of Calcutta Mathematical Society, Vol. 43 (1951), pp. 17-24.
%H A394608 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/SquareLinePicking.html">Square Line Picking</a>.
%H A394608 <a href="/index/Tra#transcendental">Index entries for transcendental numbers</a>.
%e A394608 0.512003269083333882131081199474793545179390944060415...
%t A394608 RealDigits[Root[3*x^4 - 16*x^3 + 6*Pi*x^2 - 3, 2], 10, 120][[1]]
%o A394608 (PARI) solve(x = 1/2, 1, 3*x^4 - 16*x^3 + 6*Pi*x^2 - 3)
%Y A394608 Cf. A091505 (mean), A394606 (disk), A394607 (mode).
